cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.MM

The paper is about network information theory, which is a subfield of information theory that deals with communication networks. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely sub-category as it deals with the design and analysis of communication networks. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible sub-category as it deals with the study of social networks and their properties. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely sub-category, but it could be relevant as network information theory involves analyzing the complexity of communication protocols. Finally, cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely sub-category, but it could be relevant as network information theory deals with the transmission of multimedia data over networks.
